1.2 Formatting Text

Bold: Use **text** or __text__ for bold text.
Italic: Use *text* or _text_ for italic text.
Strikethrough: Use ~~text~~ for strikethrough text.


1.2.1 Code Blocks
You can create code blocks using backticks:
print("Hello, World!")

title: My Markdown Document
text:
1.3 Conclusion
Markdown is a lightweight and easy-to-use syntax for styling text. It’s great for writing documentation, creating simple web pages, and more!
This example covers headings, text formatting, code blocks, lists, links, images, blockquotes, and tables. Let me know if you need something more specific!
